request.description:
Downloads a document as a PDF using the `documentId` variable set in request 4.

Set the response type to 'Send and Download' in Postman to save the file locally.

**Multiple documents:** If the casefile has more than one document, all IDs are available in the `documentIds` variable (JSON array). To download each one, either update `documentId` manually and re-run, or use the Postman Collection Runner with the following pre-request script to iterate:

```js
const ids = JSON.parse(pm.collectionVariables.get('documentIds'));
const index = pm.info.iteration;
pm.collectionVariables.set('documentId', ids[index]);
```

To download a JSON representation instead of a PDF, change the `Accept` header to `application/json`.
